  <p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>
</blockquote>

<ul>
  <li>Github Account</li>
  <li>HTML(Markup)/Markdown Language</li>
</ul>

<h1 id="step1-create-new-repository">Step1: Create new Repository</h1>
<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-09-05/1.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<p>After logging in Github, at the top left side, you will find the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">New</code> button as shown in the above picture.  Click the button and you will be directed to new repository page as shown below.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/blog/2019-09-05/2.PNG" alt="" /></p>

<p>Give a <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">name</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">description</code> to the repository and click to <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Create repository</code> as shown above.</p>

<!--<div markdown="span" class="alert-success" role="alert"><i class="fa fa-check-square-o"></i> <b>Tip:</b> Best name for your profile repository suits your GitHub username for eg: **yourusername.github.io** </div>-->

<div class="alert alert-success">
    <i class="fa fa-check-square-o"></i> <b>Tip:</b> Best name for your profile repository suits your GitHub username for eg: **yourusername.github.io** 
</div>

